---
<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Install</summary>
  <ol>
    <li>Make sure <strong>Python 3</strong> is installed on your Mac. Check by opening Terminal and typing <code>python3 --version</code>. If not installed, download from <a href="https://python.org">python.org</a>.</li>
    <li>Unzip and move <strong>OMF Importer.app</strong> to your Applications folder</li>
    <li>macOS will block it since it&rsquo;s not from the App Store. Right-click &rarr; <strong>Open</strong> &rarr; click <strong>Open</strong> in the dialog. You only have to do this once.</li>
  </ol>
</details>
<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Build from Source</summary>
  <ol>
    <li>Clone: <code>git clone https://github.com/justin-lawes/omf.git && cd omf/files</code></li>
    <li>Build: <code>bash build_app.sh</code></li>
    <li>Move <strong>OMF Importer.app</strong> to your Applications folder</li>
  </ol>
</details>
<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>What Gets Imported</summary>
  <ul class="tool-shortcuts">
    <li><strong>Track names</strong> Preserved from the original session</li>
    <li><strong>Track count / structure</strong> Matched to the OMF layout</li>
    <li><strong>Audio clip positions</strong> Best-effort timeline placement</li>
    <li><strong>Audio file references</strong> Linked to source files</li>
    <li><strong>MIDI regions</strong> Converted to Ableton MIDI clips</li>
    <li><strong>Volume / pan</strong> Per-track levels carried over</li>
    <li><strong>Plugin settings</strong> Not supported (OMF limitation)</li>
    <li><strong>FX chains</strong> Not supported (OMF limitation)</li>
  </ul>
</details>
